# 5.0 Docs

## SDK and MSBuild

- [Error when referencing mismatched executable](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/referencing-executable-generates-error.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 5 where compile-time errors are generated when an executable references an executable whose SelfContained value is different.
- [OutputType set to WinExe](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/automatically-infer-winexe-output-type.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET SDK 5.0.100 where OutputType is automatically set to WinExe for Windows Forms apps.
- [WinForms and WPF apps use Microsoft.NET.Sdk](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/sdk-and-target-framework-change.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 5 where Windows Forms and Windows Presentation Framework apps now use the .NET SDK instead of the .NET Core WinForms and WPF SDK.
- [Directory.Packages.props files imported by default](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/directory-packages-props-imported-by-default.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 5 where NuGet's .props files automatically import a file named Directory.Packages.props if it's found in the project folder.
- [NETCOREAPP3_1 preprocessor symbol not defined](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/netcoreapp3_1-preprocessor-symbol-not-defined.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 5 where projects no longer define preprocessor symbols for earlier versions.
- [PublishDepsFilePath behavior change](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/publishdepsfilepath-behavior-change.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 5 where the PublishDepsFilePath MSBuild property is empty for single-file applications.
- [TargetFramework change from netcoreapp to net](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/targetframework-name-change.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 5 where the value for the MSBuild TargetFramework property changed from netcoreapp3.1 to net5.0.
- [Use WindowsSdkPackageVersion for Windows SDK](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/dotnet/docs/refs/heads/llmstxt/docs/core/compatibility/sdk/5.0/override-windows-sdk-package-version.md): Learn about the breaking change in .NET 5 where the WindowsSdkPackageVersion property replaces the FrameworkReference item for overriding the version of the Windows SDK targeting package.
